        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 18 at 4:18PM EDT until July 18 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Montpelier, or
12 miles east of Hadensville, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vehicles is possible. Expect wind damage to
trees and powerlines.

This severe storm will be near...
Montpelier around 425 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Rockville, Dabneys, Gilman, Oliver, Vontay, Coatesville, Johnsons
Springs, Goodall, Locust Creek, and Mabelton.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
